<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-09-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-05-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="455" subtype="editorial-note" type="document" xml:id="d455">
                                <head><hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi></head>
                                <p>The only record that has been found of this meeting, aside from
                                    the entry in the Log, <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_660">p. 660</ref>, is the reference to it which
                                    appears in a telegram of December 12, 1943, from the Ambassador
                                    to the Greek Government-in-Exile in Egypt (<persName corresp="#p_ML1">MacVeagh</persName>) to the Secretary of
                                    State, <hi rend="italic">post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_844">p.
                                        844</ref>.</p>
                            </div>
